This paper discusses the adaptation of data warehouses to changes in data sources and analysis requirements, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). It also deals with the processing of big data, which is a topic of interest in distributed computing (cs.DC) and machine learning (cs.DL). The paper proposes a data warehouse architecture that involves metadata management, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper discusses the evolution of data warehouses, which is a topic of interest in software engineering (cs.SE).
